							"score": 5,
							"reviewDescription": "Shadow point is a 4-dimensional puzzle platformer game. You access the 4th dimension through special doorways or a mirror/looking glass. The puzzles are solved by casting shadows with special objects. Some of these objects are also 4-dimensional, and you can rotate them in the 4th dimension to change their 3D appearance (so they cast a different 2D shadow!) with the mirrors/doorways/looking glass. Additionally, sometimes when you walk through a doorway gravity changes direction.\n\nShadow Point is not as difficult as I've made it sound just now, and was absolutely a blast the whole time. The narration and storyline give good cues as to how to play and think about the puzzles. You have the option to move or teleport, but I found areas in the environment where it was hard to move without walking (I prefer teleporting to avoid motion sickness), such as around stairs. Sometimes solving a puzzle required some awkward stretching or hand positioning but this is naturally part of the game. I enjoyed the game enough that even with these inconveniences I am rating it 5 stars.\n\nOverall Shadow Point is an excellent demonstration of developing experiences that take advantage of unique VR opportunities not available on traditional video game platforms. I would buy a sequel with no hesitation.",
